The strategic plan includes closing outdated plants, investing in modern facilities, and leveraging leading co-manufacturing partners. The company will invest $230 million in newer facilities, creating 210 new roles.

headline: As Federal Marijuana Reclassification Is Poised To Take Effect, These States Focus On Cannabis Reform
summary: In Massachusetts, the eliminated rule under which all marijuana deliveries are to be handled by two drivers is still enforced, according to CommonWealth Beacon's Bhaamati Borkhetaria.Last week, a measure that seeks to put an end to federal marijuana enforcement in legal states - the Strengthening the Tenth Amendment Through Entrusting States (STATES) 2.0 Act – got an endorsement from The Peace Officers Research Association of California (PORAC) and the Oregon Coalition of Police and Sheriffs (ORCOPs), reported Marijuana Moment.New Hampshire Senators gave the green light to a marijuana legalization measure on Thursday, following an initial floor vote earlier this month. The approval followed some major changes to the measure that now heads to the state's House of Representatives for concurrence on recent amendments, reported Marijuana Moment.Meanwhile, Senators in Louisiana approved the amended version of HB 165. The measure from state Rep. Delisha Boyd (D- New Orleans) seeks to decriminalize marijuana and the use of drug paraphernalia, reported KTVE.
